text.section:
Where husband and wife have not separately reported and claimed items of income and adjustments of income for federal income tax purposes, and have not elected to file a joint Kentucky income tax return, such items allowable for Kentucky income tax purposes shall be allocated and adjusted as follows:
Income shall be allocated to the spouse who earned the income or with respect to whose property the income is attributable;
Allowable deductions with respect to trade, business, or production of income shall be allocated to the spouse to whom attributable.
